Thought:
(1) The two floors of the human resources department and the sales department are not adjacent;
(2) The finance department is on the next floor of the planning department;
(3) The floor of the administrative department is above the planning department, but in the manpower Below the Resources Department.
From clue (2), we know that the finance department is on one of the floors immediately above or below the planning department. From clue (3), we know that the administrative department is above the planning department, but below the human resources department. Therefore, the administrative department must be on the floor immediately above the planning department, and the human resources department must be on one of the two floors above the administrative department. From clue (1), we know that the sales department is not on one of the two floors adjacent to the human resources department, so it must be on one of the two floors above the human resources department. Finally, the research and development department must be on the remaining floor.
Action: Answer("B") - Finance Department, Planning Department, Administration Department, Human Resources Department, Sales Department, R & D Department
